    <tr>


      <td align="justify">Reduces the number of transactions. Uses
different techniques and parameters for selection&nbsp; considering
that reduction can be made the&nbsp; by rank as by value. Transactions
are selected&nbsp; by the attribute wheter is a number or wheter
alphabetical value.<br>
      <br>
Reduction by Rank: This technique is in charge to reduce&nbsp; the
input set, in a rank of transactions, from one&nbsp; initial
transaction to a final one according to the parameter chosen by&nbsp;
the analyst, which can be: to delete or keep these transactions.&nbsp; <br>
      <br>
Reduction of Transactions by Attribute:&nbsp; This technique is in
charge to reduce to the input set, depending&nbsp; on the data type
that contains the selected attribute, which&nbsp; can be alphabetical
or numerical, if&nbsp; numerical, a numerical limit must be provide
if&nbsp; alphabetical, the analyst can select the attributes of his
interest.&nbsp; In addition, according to the parameter selected by the
analyst, the filter&nbsp;&nbsp; will delete or keep the selected
transactions.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>
      <br>
